Head (Figs 7, 14
B-E
) widest posterior 0.3, not subparallel in posterior half, dorsolaterally with a pair of moderately long setae and one pair near the frontoclypeal suture (Fig. 14B); lateral setae of various size, very short to moderately long. Frontal suture inconspicuous; subbasal fringe of clypeus with rather short fasciculate setae. Ventral side (Fig. 14D) dominantly rugulose; basolateral areas and genae (inbetween setae) glabrous (Fig. 14C).
